.

Body length of the examined specimens varied from 8.0 to 
10.5 mm
(males) and from 7.0 to 9.0 mm (females). Head and pronotum armature in males varied from well-developed with long lateral pronotal processes and frontoclypeal horn (
Fig. 2A
) to excavated pronotum with gibbosities aside of the excavation and frontoclypeal tubercle (
Fig. 2C
), with intermediate variants (
Fig. 2B
).

The species is distributed rather widely on 
Sri Lanka
except for the eastern part (
Fig. 1H
).
